Name: Yosemite National Park
Description: Yosemite is a U.S. National Park located in Northern California. Yosemite is known for its towering granite walls and picturesque valley floor.

Name: Foothills Nature Preserve
Description: 1,400-acre park and nature preserve in the Santa Cruz Mountains of California, United States, within the city of Palo Alto

Name: Twin Peaks
Description: Twin Peaks is a 64-acre hilltop park named for the pair of 922-foot-high hills that sit at the center of the park. The park is situated in near the center of SF in a highly resedential area of the city.

Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Poplar Beach
Description: Poplar Beach is a beach located in Half Moon Bay, California. It's a wide open stretch of beautiful sandy coastline that stretchs for about two miles.

Name: Lands End Park
Description: Lands End is a park in the most north western corner of the city. It borders the Pacific Ocean with beautiful lookouts of the ocean and the Golden Gate Bridge.
